  "title": "Queue Versus Capacity Collapse",
  "concept": "When demand arrives faster than a fixed-capacity system can process it, the queue either stabilizes if arrivals slow below throughput or collapses into chaos if the backlog grows faster than the system clears it, forcing closure to reset flow.",
  "interactiveId": "9040c65b-92fa-4899-bfa6-3752508e3936",
  "sourcePieceId": "37119a9e-0e3e-4c98-83bc-55b4f9b07b27",
  "publishedAt": 1778991941486,
  "voiceScore": 95,
  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Queue Versus Capacity Collapse</title>\n<style>\n* { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }\nbody {\n  font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;\n  background: #f8f9fa;\n  padding: 20px;\n  color: #1a1a1a;\n}\n.container {\n  max-width: 700px;\n  margin: 0 auto;\n  background: white;\n  padding: 30px;\n  border-radius: 8px;\n  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\n}\nh1 {\n  font-size: 24px;\n  font-weight: 600;\n  margin-bottom: 8px;\n  color: #1a1a1a;\n}\n.concept {\n  font-size: 15px;\n  line-height: 1.5;\n  color: #4a5568;\n  margin-bottom: 30px;\n  padding-bottom: 20px;\n  border-bottom: 1px solid #e2e8f0;\n}\n.controls {\n  margin-bottom: 25px;\n}\n.control-group {\n  margin-bottom: 20px;\n}\nlabel {\n  display: block;\n  font-size: 14px;\n  font-weight: 500;\n  margin-bottom: 8px;\n  color: #2d3748;\n}\n.slider-container {\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  gap: 12px;\n}\ninput[type=\"range\"] {\n  flex: 1;\n  height: 6px;\n  border-radius: 3px;\n  background: #e2e8f0;\n  outline: none;\n  -webkit-appearance: none;\n}\ninput[type=\"range\"]::-webkit-slider-thumb {\n  -webkit-appearance: none;\n  appearance: none;\n  width: 18px;\n  height: 18px;\n  border-radius: 50%;\n  background: #3182ce;\n  cursor: pointer;\n}\ninput[type=\"range\"]::-moz-range-thumb {\n  width: 18px;\n  height: 18px;\n  border-radius: 50%;\n  background: #3182ce;\n  cursor: pointer;\n  border: none;\n}\n.value-display {\n  font-size: 14px;\n  font-weight: 600;\n  color: #2d3748;\n  min-width: 80px;\n  text-align: right;\n}\n.simulation {\n  background: #f7fafc;\n  border: 2px solid #e2e8f0;\n  border-radius: 6px;\n  padding: 20px;\n  margin-bottom: 20px;\n}\n.sim-header {\n  display: flex;\n  justify-content: space-between;\n  align-items: center;\n  margin-bottom: 15px;\n}\n.sim-title {\n  font-size: 14px;\n  font-weight: 600;\n  color: #2d3748;\n}\n.status {\n  font-size: 13px;\n  padding: 4px 12px;\n  border-radius: 12px;\n  font-weight: 500;\n}\n.status.stable {\n  background: #c6f6d5;\n  color: #22543d;\n}\n.status.warning {\n  background: #fef5e7;\n  color: #975a16;\n}\n.status.collapsed {\n  background: #fed7d7;\n  color: #742a2a;\n}\n.queue-viz {\n  height: 200px;\n  position: relative;\n  background: white;\n  border-radius: 4px;\n  overflow: hidden;\n}\n.person {\n  position: absolute;\n  width: 20px;\n  height: 30px;\n  background: #4299e1;\n  border-radius: 3px;\n  transition: all 0.3s ease;\n}\n.person.processed {\n  background: #48bb78;\n}\n.person.overflow {\n  background: #f56565;\n}\n.metrics {\n  display: grid;\n  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;\n  gap: 15px;\n  margin-top: 15px;\n}\n.metric {\n  text-align: center;\n  padding: 10px;\n  background: white;\n  border-radius: 4px;\n}\n.metric-value {\n  font-size: 24px;\n  font-weight: 700;\n  color: #2d3748;\n  margin-bottom: 4px;\n}\n.metric-label {\n  font-size: 12px;\n  color: #718096;\n  text-transform: uppercase;\n  letter-spacing: 0.5px;\n}\n.explanation {\n  font-size: 14px;\n  line-height: 1.6;\n  color: #4a5568;\n  background: #edf2f7;\n  padding: 15px;\n  border-radius: 6px;\n  border-left: 3px solid #3182ce;\n}\n@media (max-width: 600px) {\n  .container { padding: 20px; }\n  h1 { font-size: 20px; }\n  .metrics { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }\n}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div class=\"container\">\n  <h1>Queue Versus Capacity Collapse</h1>\n  <p class=\"concept\">When demand arrives faster than a fixed-capacity system can process it, the queue either stabilizes if arrivals slow below throughput or collapses into chaos if the backlog grows faster than the system clears it, forcing closure to reset flow.</p>\n  \n  <div class=\"controls\">\n    <div class=\"control-group\">\n      <label>Arrival rate (people per minute)</label>\n      <div class=\"slider-container\">\n        <input type=\"range\" id=\"arrivalRate\" min=\"5\" max=\"50\" value=\"15\" step=\"1\">\n        <span class=\"value-display\" id=\"arrivalValue\">15/min</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"control-group\">\n      <label>Processing capacity (people per minute)</label>\n      <div class=\"slider-container\">\n        <input type=\"range\" id=\"capacity\" min=\"5\" max=\"50\" value=\"20\" step=\"1\">\n        <span class=\"value-display\" id=\"capacityValue\">20/min</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  \n  <div class=\"simulation\">\n    <div class=\"sim-header\">\n      <span class=\"sim-title\">Queue state over 2 minutes</span>\n      <span class=\"status stable\" id=\"status\">Stable</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"queue-viz\" id=\"queueViz\"></div>\n    <div class=\"metrics\">\n      <div class=\"metric\">\n        <div class=\"metric-value\" id=\"queueSize\">0</div>\n        <div class=\"metric-label\">In queue</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"metric\">\n        <div class=\"metric-value\" id=\"processed\">0</div>\n        <div class=\"metric-label\">Served</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"metric\">\n        <div class=\"metric-value\" id=\"overflow\">0</div>\n        <div class=\"metric-label\">Turned away</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  \n  <div class=\"explanation\" id=\"explanation\">\n    When arrivals match or fall below capacity, the queue drains steadily. The system stays stable.\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<script>\nconst arrivalSlider = document.getElementById('arrivalRate');\nconst capacitySlider = document.getElementById('capacity');\nconst arrivalValue = document.getElementById('arrivalValue');\nconst capacityValue = document.getElementById('capacityValue');\nconst status = document.getElementById('status');\nconst queueViz = document.getElementById('queueViz');\nconst queueSizeDisplay = document.getElementById('queueSize');\nconst processedDisplay = document.getElementById('processed');\nconst overflowDisplay = document.getElementById('overflow');\nconst explanation = document.getElementById('explanation');\n\nlet arrivalRate = 15;\nlet capacity = 20;\nlet queue = [];\nlet processed = 0;\nlet overflow = 0;\nlet time = 0;\nlet animationId = null;\nconst MAX_QUEUE = 40;\nconst SIM_DURATION = 120;\n\nfunction updateDisplays() {\n  arrivalValue.textContent = arrivalRate + '/min';\n  capacityValue.textContent = capacity + '/min';\n}\n\nfunction resetSimulation() {\n  queue = [];\n  processed = 0;\n  overflow = 0;\n  time = 0;\n  if (animationId) cancelAnimationFrame(animationId);\n  runSimulation();\n}\n\nfunction runSimulation() {\n  const step = () => {\n    if (time >= SIM_DURATION) {\n      updateVisuals();\n      return;\n    }\n    \n    time++;\n    \n    const arrivals = Math.floor(arrivalRate / 60 + Math.random());\n    for (let i = 0; i < arrivals; i++) {\n      if (queue.length < MAX_QUEUE) {\n        queue.push({ id: Date.now() + Math.random(), time: time });\n      } else {\n        overflow++;\n      }\n    }\n    \n    const canProcess = Math.min(Math.floor(capacity / 60 + Math.random()), queue.length);\n    for (let i = 0; i < canProcess; i++) {\n      queue.shift();\n      processed++;\n    }\n    \n    updateVisuals();\n    animationId = requestAnimationFrame(step);\n  };\n  \n  step();\n}\n\nfunction updateVisuals() {\n  queueSizeDisplay.textContent = queue.length;\n  processedDisplay.textContent = processed;\n  overflowDisplay.textContent = overflow;\n  \n  const ratio = arrivalRate / capacity;\n  if (ratio < 0.9) {\n    status.className = 'status stable';\n    status.textContent = 'Stable';\n    explanation.textContent = 'When arrivals fall below capacity, the queue drains steadily. The system stays stable.';\n  } else if (ratio < 1.1) {\n    status.className = 'status warning';\n    status.textContent = 'Balanced';\n    explanation.textContent = 'When arrivals match capacity, the queue hovers near zero but can spike with random variation. The system is fragile.';\n  } else {\n    status.className = 'status collapsed';\n    status.textContent = 'Collapsed';\n    explanation.textContent = 'When arrivals exceed capacity, the backlog grows faster than the system can clear it. The queue fills, overflow builds, and closure becomes the only way to reset flow.';\n  }\n  \n  queueViz.innerHTML = '';\n  const vizWidth = queueViz.offsetWidth;\n  const vizHeight = queueViz.offsetHeight;\n  const cols = Math.floor(vizWidth / 25);\n  const rows = Math.floor(vizHeight / 35);\n  const maxDisplay = cols * rows;\n  \n  queue.slice(0, maxDisplay).forEach((person, i) => {\n    const col = i % cols;\n    const row = Math.floor(i / cols);\n    const div = document.createElement('div');\n    div.className = 'person';\n    div.style.left = (col * 25 + 2) + 'px';\n    div.style.top = (row * 35 + 2) + 'px';\n    queueViz.appendChild(div);\n  });\n  \n  if (queue.length > maxDisplay) {\n    const indicator = document.createElement('div');\n    indicator.style.position = 'absolute';\n    indicator.style.bottom = '10px';\n    indicator.style.right = '10px';\n    indicator.style.fontSize = '12px';\n    indicator.style.fontWeight = '600';\n    indicator.style.color = '#e53e3e';\n    indicator.textContent = '+' + (queue.length - maxDisplay) + ' more';\n    queueViz.appendChild(indicator);\n  }\n}\n\narrivalSlider.addEventListener('input', (e) => {\n  arrivalRate = parseInt(e.target.value);\n  updateDisplays();\n  resetSimulation();\n  window.parent.postMessage({type: 'interactive_engagement', event: 'manipulated'}, '*');\n});\n\ncapacitySlider.addEventListener('input', (e) => {\n  capacity = parseInt(e.target.value);\n  updateDisplays();\n  resetSimulation();\n  window.parent.postMessage({type: 'interactive_engagement', event: 'manipulated'}, '*');\n});\n\nupdateDisplays();\nrunSimulation();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
